Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest queue

Purpose:
  Manage device-local `.sdpub` graph and summary jobs.

Usage:
  spinedigest queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> [--to graph|summary] [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  spinedigest queue list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive.sdpub>]
  spinedigest queue status <job-id>
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  spinedigest queue pause <job-id>
  spinedigest queue resume <job-id>
  spinedigest queue cancel <job-id>
  spinedigest queue boost <job-id>
  spinedigest queue target <job-id> --to graph|summary
  spinedigest queue clean

Scheduling:
  New jobs are appended to the queue by default.
  Use `--boost` on add, or `queue boost <job-id>`, to move a queued job to the front.
  Boosting does not preempt currently running jobs.

Targets:
  `graph` builds topology for one chapter.
  `summary` builds graph if needed, then builds the chapter summary.
  Downgrading from summary to graph is allowed only before summary starts.

Watch:
  TTY output is human-readable.
  `--jsonl` prints one structured event per line and is the recommended mode for agents.
